article.headline: Jacksonville 80, Stetson 74
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Haminn Quaintance scored 21 points and grabbed 12 rebounds to lead Jacksonville to an 80-74 win over Stetson on Tuesday night. Quaintance recorded his fifth double-double of the year and led a second-half surge following Stetson's 42-40 lead at halftime. The freshman ignited an 11-2 Jacksonville run during a three minute span midway in the second half with back-to-back slam dunks. David Lee hit a 3-pointer and Nolan McBride added a pair of baskets to complete the run, which gave Jacksonville (8-10, 3-8 Atlantic Sun) a 56-48 lead it never relinquished. It was the Dolphins second conference win in four days after losing their previous six league games. Jacksonville had five players in double figures for a second straight game. Aubrey Conerly scored 17 points while David Lee had 13. Jarred Stockton added 12 points off the bench while McBride finished with 10 points. The Hatters (7-10, 5-6) were led by Anthony Register and Gabe McMillen who had 19 points apiece. Kevin Craig added 13 points and 10 rebounds for Stetson.
